# Week 2 — Market Data Pipeline Implementation Plan

Build the complete market data ingestion pipeline: Fyers API live ticks + yfinance fallback → Polars cleaning → ClickHouse bulk insert, orchestrated by Celery Beat + Prefect, with Redis caching and Postgres seeding.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Fyers API Credentials**: The [.env](file:///e:/terminal_proj/.env) has empty `FYERS_APP_ID`, `FYERS_SECRET`, and `FYERS_ACCESS_TOKEN`. You'll need to register at [myapi.fyers.in](https://myapi.fyers.in) and fill these in. The auth module I'll build handles token refresh, but initial credentials must be set manually.

> [!WARNING]
> **Fyers API on Windows**: The Fyers OAuth2 flow requires a redirect URI. The auth script will spin up a local Flask server to capture the callback. You need to set `http://127.0.0.1:8765` as your redirect URL in the Fyers app dashboard.

> [!NOTE]
> **yfinance as primary for now**: Since Fyers credentials are empty, the pipeline will use yfinance as the primary data source out of the box. Fyers will activate automatically once credentials are configured. yfinance uses `.NS` suffix for NSE tickers (e.g., `RELIANCE.NS`).

---

