### Fyers Authentication

#### [NEW] [fyers_auth.py](file:///e:/terminal_proj/ingestion/market/fyers_auth.py)
- `generate_auth_url()` → builds OAuth2 URL with app_id + redirect
- `start_auth_server()` → Flask micro-server on port 8765 to capture auth code
- `exchange_code_for_token(auth_code)` → POST to Fyers token endpoint
- `get_or_refresh_token()` → checks if stored token is valid, refreshes if expired
- Token persisted to `.fyers_token.json` (gitignored)

---

### Market Data Fetchers

#### [MODIFY] [fyers_downloader.py](file:///e:/terminal_proj/ingestion/market/fyers_downloader.py)
- `FyersDownloader` class
- `fetch_quotes(symbols: list[str])` → live quote snapshot (LTP, volume, timestamp)
- `fetch_historical(symbol, resolution, from_date, to_date)` → historical OHLCV
- Returns `list[dict]` normalized to `{symbol, price, volume, timestamp}` format
- Uses `fyers_apiv3.FyersModel` under the hood

#### [MODIFY] [yfinance_downloader.py](file:///e:/terminal_proj/ingestion/market/yfinance_downloader.py)
- `YFinanceDownloader` class
- `fetch_quotes(symbols: list[str])` → current price via `yf.Ticker.fast_info`
- `fetch_historical(symbol, period, interval)` → historical OHLCV via `yf.download()`
- Returns same normalized format as Fyers for drop-in fallback
- Handles `.NS` suffix mapping for NSE tickers

---

### Data Cleaning Pipeline

#### [NEW] [polars_pipeline.py](file:///e:/terminal_proj/ingestion/market/polars_pipeline.py)
- `clean_ticks(raw: list[dict]) → pl.DataFrame` 
  - Cast types (symbol→Utf8, price→Float64, volume→Float64, timestamp→Datetime)
  - Drop nulls, filter price > 0, dedup on (symbol, timestamp)
  - Sort by (symbol, timestamp)
- `df_to_clickhouse_rows(df: pl.DataFrame) → list[list]`
  - Convert Polars DF to row-oriented format for ClickHouse insert

---

### Database Helpers

#### [MODIFY] [clickhouse_client.py](file:///e:/terminal_proj/db/clickhouse_client.py)
- `insert_ticks(rows: list[list])` → bulk insert into `market_ticks`
- `get_latest_ticks(symbol, limit)` → query recent ticks
- `get_ohlcv(symbol, timeframe, start, end)` → query OHLCV from MVs
- `get_row_count(table)` → diagnostic helper

#### [NEW] [redis_cache.py](file:///e:/terminal_proj/db/redis_cache.py)
- `cache_latest_prices(prices: dict[str, float])` → SET each symbol with TTL 60s
- `get_cached_price(symbol) → float | None` → GET with parse
- `get_all_cached_prices() → dict` → SCAN for all cached prices
- Key format: `price:{symbol}`

---

### Celery App & Tasks

#### [NEW] [celery_app.py](file:///e:/terminal_proj/celery_app.py)
- `app = Celery("atlas", broker=settings.CELERY_BROKER_URL)`
- Beat schedule: `fetch-market-ticks` every 60s
- Timezone: `Asia/Kolkata`

#### [NEW] [market_tasks.py](file:///e:/terminal_proj/tasks/market_tasks.py)
- `@app.task fetch_and_store_ticks()`
  - Check if within market hours (9:15–15:30 IST)
  - Try Fyers first, fallback to yfinance
  - Clean via Polars pipeline
  - Bulk insert into ClickHouse
  - Cache latest prices in Redis
  - Log count of inserted rows

---

### Prefect Orchestration

#### [NEW] [market_flow.py](file:///e:/terminal_proj/flows/market_flow.py)
- `@flow eod_data_pipeline()`
  - Fetch full-day OHLCV for all NIFTY 50 symbols
  - Clean + insert into ClickHouse
  - Log summary stats
- `@flow backfill_historical(days_back=30)`
  - Fetch historical data for specified lookback
  - Bulk insert into ClickHouse
- Schedule: daily at 16:00 IST (after market close)

---

